Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Editor pane wiring on top of Batch 1's data layer:

- KrtDiffFileTree (new) replaces the flat-list file column in the
  Diff sub-mode and the Storyboard chapter panel. Real folder
  tree with collapsible folders, per-folder counts (files, +/-),
  and an inline mark-reviewed checkbox on each row. Single-child
  folder runs compact into one row (`a/b/c.rs` is one row when
  every intermediate folder has only one child), mirroring
  `tree --collapse` and the demo. Collapsed folder set persists
  per-PR via IStorageService.

- Filename click hands off to the Editor view (Phase 9): opens
  the file via IEditorService.openEditor in SIDE_GROUP, using
  the workspace's real file:// URI when checked out, falling
  back to a krt-git:// URI bound to pr.head.sha when not. The
  per-row "scroll to file" affordance preserves the previous
  scroll-into-diff behaviour for users who want it.

- Tour Reading mode drops its 880px max-width — it cramps wide
  monitors and the diff editors inside read better at full pane
  width.

- Tour mini-diffs and the Storyboard chapter diff now thread the
  chapter's `chips` through to KrtPrFlatDiff. The main Diff
  surface gets the union of every chapter's chips since it has
  no current-chapter context.

- Storyboard graph filters out the synthetic Coverage chapter:
  it has no dependsOn edges by design, so it would render as a
  visually loud free-floating card.

Demo: open a Rust PR, browse the diff with the tree and a
collapsed folder; click a filename → Editor view opens that
file with rust-analyzer; flip to Tour, see Coverage at the end
walking untouched lines, and chips inside the diff at the lines
the model called out.
